abstract: A flush of wealth and an influx of business travelers have given rise to distinctive, imaginative restaurants. A list of standouts captures the variety of China’s new scene.
snippet: A flush of wealth and an influx of business travelers have given rise to distinctive, imaginative restaurants. A list of standouts captures the variety of China’s new scene.
lead_paragraph: SHANGHAI — Some restaurants place you close to the surf, its perfume in the air and its music in your ears, while others nestle you in the woods. Some put you next to the Seine, others beside aquariums bursting with tropical colors.

abstract: Inspired by a book written in 1790, a photographer set out to capture the vast differences between Russia’s cities and its hinterlands.
snippet: Inspired by a book written in 1790, a photographer set out to capture the vast differences between Russia’s cities and its hinterlands.
lead_paragraph: A year and a half ago, the photographer Dmitry Kostyukov came to me with an idea: to document the road journey between St. Petersburg and Moscow, an abysmal stretch more easily hopped by air or high-speed rail, and seldom traveled by anyone with the money or privilege to avoid it.
headline_main: Down a Road Less Traveled, Looking for the Still Heart of Russia

abstract: Providers of educational technology can mine the data of young children, but privacy groups are trying to set up barriers.
snippet: Providers of educational technology can mine the data of young children, but privacy groups are trying to set up barriers.
lead_paragraph: A leading children’s advocacy group is challenging the educational technology software industry, an estimated $8 billion market, to develop national safeguards for the personal data collected about students from kindergarten through high school.

abstract: Older parents discuss their strategies and approaches when it comes to drinking by the newer generation’s teenagers.
snippet: Older parents discuss their strategies and approaches when it comes to drinking by the newer generation’s teenagers.
lead_paragraph: This past week’s topic for New Parent/Old Parent was teenage drinking and how to deal with it as a parent (and there were comments). The first thing that struck me was that in all my time moderating reader comments, I can’t remember so many as lengthy and nuanced — an indication, I think, on how complex and difficult the issue is and how much it can vary from child to child and from family to family. I was also touched by how many of the responses conveyed a sense of parental humility. I have worked hard to be a very good parent, but boy, did I fail on this front … a lot.

snippet: Representative Paul D. Ryan, the defeated 2012 vice-presidential nominee, drafted a debt ceiling proposal that fellow Republicans embraced, though it doesn’t mention President Obama’s health care law.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Representative Paul D. Ryan may have temporarily receded into the Capitol shadows after his stinging vice-presidential defeat in November, but he remains a powerful presence among House Republicans, earning the respect of hard-line conservatives for his budget blueprint and the trust of anxious moderates for his pragmatism.

abstract: A 12-year-old boy falls in love with his neighbor’s derelict 1977 Volkswagen camper van, and after much persistence, and bartering some yard work, brings the van home.
snippet: A 12-year-old boy falls in love with his neighbor’s derelict 1977 Volkswagen camper van, and after much persistence, and bartering some yard work, brings the van home.
lead_paragraph: Sitting in the living room of her family’s 19th-century colonial home, Lesley Fowks recalled the day in 2002 that her son, Ian Brady, burst in with an announcement: the rusting 1977 Volkswagen camper van sitting in the side yard of a nearby house could be his “for free.”
